node-red-contrib-multiflexi (0.3.6) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Restore NODE_PATH systemd drop-in (node-red.service.d/node-red-nodepath.conf)
    required for node-red itself to locate @node-red/* packages under
    /usr/share/node-red at startup.
  * Install contrib to /usr/share/nodejs/ and create userDir symlink in postinst
    (/var/lib/node-red/.node-red/node_modules/node-red-contrib-multiflexi)
    so node-red palette loader discovers the nodes without any NODE_PATH tricks.
  * postrm: remove the userDir symlink on package removal.
  * Bundle body-parser and cookie-parser node_modules (the only runtime deps).

 -- Vítězslav Dvořák <info@vitexsoftware.cz>  Thu, 19 Jun 2026 14:00:00 +0200

node-red-contrib-multiflexi (0.3.5) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Do not bundle node_modules/: all runtime deps (node-red, @node-red/*)
    are already present as deb packages under /usr/share/node-red/node_modules/.
    Bundling them caused node-red to crash with MODULE_NOT_FOUND on startup
    because the nested copies shadowed node-red's own scoped packages.

 -- Vítězslav Dvořák <info@vitexsoftware.cz>  Thu, 19 Jun 2026 11:00:00 +0200

node-red-contrib-multiflexi (0.3.4) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Install module files directly to /usr/share/node-red/node_modules/ so
